i>, given to the apostle  Simon  son of Jona, to distinguish him from another of the same name (  Simon Zelotes ). ‘When Jesus beheld him, he said, Thou art Simon the son of Jona: thou shalt be called Cephas, which is by interpretation, A stone’ (John 1:42). According to Matthew 16:17–18, Christ says more explicitly, ‘Blessed art thou, Simon Bar-jona … thou art Peter, and upon this rock I will build my church’. The name has been in continuous use since the Middle Ages."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Pierre I de Rostrenen was born about 1097, in Rostrenen, Côtes-du-Nord, Brittany, France, his father, Derrien Rostrenen Seigneur de Rostrenen, was 32 and his mother, Mrs Derrien de Rostrenen, was 32. He married Mrs. Pierre I de Rostenen about 1135, in Rostrenen, Côtes-du-Nord, Brittany, France. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 4 daughters. He died in his hometown."},"et":{"Abt 1097–":"umbes 1097–Surnud","1097–Male":"1097–Surnud","1110–Female":"1110–Surnud","1137–Male":"1137–Surnud","1167–1241":"1167–1241","1169–Female":"1169–Surnud","1171–Female":"1171–Surnud","1175–1214":"1175–1214","1067–Male":"1067–Surnud","1067–Female":"1067–Surnud","before 1135":"enne 1135","1110":"1110","1175":"1175","1241":"1241","Abt 1137":"umbes 1137","1097":"1097","Abt 1169":"umbes 1169","1171":"1171","Abt 1097":"umbes 1097","1214":"1214","1137":"1137","Abt 1135":"umbes 1135","1169":"1169","Abt 1167":"umbes 1167","1167":"1167","22 JAN 1175":"22. jaanuar 1175","1067":"1067","Abt 1171":"umbes 1171","Rostrenen, Côtes-d'Armor, Brittany, France":"Rostrenen, Côtes-du-Nord, Bretagne, Prantsusmaa","Brittany, France":"Bretagne, Prantsusmaa","Rostrenen,22266,Côtes-d'Armor,Bretagne,FRANCE,":"Rostrenen, Côtes-du-Nord, Bretagne, Prantsusmaa","Rostrenen, Côtes-d'Armor, Bretagne, France":"Rostrenen, Côtes-du-Nord, Bretagne, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"Abt 1097–":"noin 1097–Kuollut","1097–Male":"1097–Kuollut","1110–Female":"1110–Kuollut","1137–Male":"1137–Kuollut","1167–1241":"1167–1241","1169–Female":"1169–Kuo